info.description:
E2E tests for DELETE /api/v1/profile/me and POST /api/v1/profile/me/cancel-deletion (both require JWT).

Folder execution order (orchestrated by make e2e-delete-account — all in ONE Newman invocation):
  1. setup                — register gmail_test_email (del_user_a) and gmail_test_email+delb (del_user_b),
                            fetch verification OTPs from Gmail, verify and login both users
  2. happy-path-password  — Path A (T-01, T-20, T-34): DELETE with password → 200; GET /me session-live check;
                            POST /auth/login pending-deletion login check; repeat DELETE → 409
  3. happy-path-cancel         — T-27: POST /cancel-deletion → 200; GET /me scheduled_deletion_at absent;
                                 repeat cancel → 409 not_pending_deletion
  4. happy-path-deletion-method — GET /me/deletion-method: password user → 200;
                                 no JWT → 401; pending account → 409
  5. happy-path-email-otp       — B-path wire-checks (T-10): DELETE {code} with no active OTP → 422 token_not_found;
                                 DELETE {invalid code format} → 422 validation_error
  6. telegram-guards            — T-14 / T-15: DELETE with stale auth_date → 401 invalid_telegram_auth;
                                 DELETE with id=0 → 400 validation_error
  7. failures                   — DELETE wrong password → 401 invalid_credentials;
                                 DELETE empty body (password user) → 400 validation_error
  8. auth-failures              — missing / tampered Authorization for DELETE and POST cancel
  9. validation                 — body > 1 MiB → 413 for both endpoints; malformed JSON → 400 for both
  10. rate-limiting-del         — del:usr: (10 req/1hr): register +delrl alias, 10 warmup DELETEs + cancels, 11th → 429
  11. rate-limiting-delc        — delc:usr: (10 req/10min): register +cncrl alias, 10 warmup cancels, 11th → 429

Rate-limiter invocation decision:
  Both del:usr: and delc:usr: sit INSIDE the r.Use(deps.JWTAuth) middleware group.
  Running either rate-limiting folder in a separate Newman invocation loses the access token
  stored in collection variables, causing 401 (unauthorized) instead of 429 (too_many_requests).
  All 10 folders therefore run in a single Newman invocation. Redis is flushed once before
  the run so all buckets start empty. The rate-limiting folders pin _xff to 127.0.0.1 by
  convention; the actual bucketing is user-keyed so _xff has no effect on the RL decision.

Gmail aliases used:
  del_user_a  : gmail_test_email (primary inbox)
  del_user_b  : gmail_test_email+delb (B-path wire-checks)
  delrl user  : gmail_test_email+delrl (fresh del:usr: bucket)
  cncrl user  : gmail_test_email+cncrl (fresh delc:usr: bucket)

// NOT covered here (covered by unit/integration tests):
//
// - T-02 (B-1: email-OTP user, empty body → 202 "verification code sent"):
//     Requires a user with has_password=false. Creating such a user requires
//     a real OAuth callback. Covered by service_test.go T-02, handler_test.go T-02.
//
// - T-03 (B-2: email-OTP step 2 happy path → 200 with scheduled_deletion_at):
//     Same reason — needs a no-password user with an active OTP token.
//     Covered by service_test.go T-03, handler_test.go T-03.
//
// - T-04 (C-1: Telegram-only user, empty body → 202 auth_method:telegram):
//     Requires a Telegram-only account (no email, no password). Creating one
//     requires a real Telegram OAuth callback with a bot-signed HMAC payload.
//     Covered by service_test.go T-04, handler_test.go T-04.
//
// - T-05 (C-2: Telegram step 2 happy path → 200):
//     Same reason — requires a valid live HMAC payload from Telegram's servers
//     and a properly linked Telegram identity.
//     Covered by service_test.go T-05, handler_test.go T-05.
//
// - T-08 (wrong password → 401 invalid_credentials):
//     Confirmed in the failures folder. Additional variants (empty password,
//     all-whitespace) covered by handler_test.go.
//
// - T-10 / T-11 (token_not_found / token_already_used in happy B-2 path):
//     Require precise DB state (consumed token). The token_not_found wire-check
//     IS covered (folder 4 — no active OTP for password user). token_already_used
//     requires issuing and consuming the same token twice atomically, which is
//     not reliable in Newman. Covered by service_test.go T-10/T-11.
//
// - T-12 (wrong OTP code with attempts < max → 422 invalid_code):
//     Requires a no-password user with an active OTP. Not achievable without OAuth.
//     Covered by service_test.go T-12.
//
// - T-13 (OTP attempt budget exhausted → 429 too_many_attempts):
//     Requires 3 consecutive wrong OTP submissions. Not reliable without a real OTP.
//     Covered by service_test.go T-13, handler_test.go T-13.
//
// - T-16 (telegram_identity_mismatch → 401):
//     Requires a Telegram-linked account where provider_uid !== submitted id.
//     Not achievable without a real Telegram identity. Covered by service_test.go T-16.
//
// - T-18 / T-19 (sessions and tokens NOT revoked after soft-delete):
//     Partially confirmed by GET /me returning 200 post-delete in happy-path-password.
//     Full DB-level assertion (ended_at IS NULL, revoked_at IS NULL) covered by
//     store_test.go T-18/T-19.
//
// - T-21 / T-22 / T-23 / T-30 (context.WithoutCancel usage):
//     Not testable via HTTP. Covered by service_test.go.
//
// - T-24 / T-25 / T-31 (store errors → 500 internal_error):
//     Require DB error injection. Covered by handler_test.go and integration tests.
//
// - T-32 / T-33 (GET /me scheduled_deletion_at present / absent):
//     Confirmed as a side-effect assertion in happy-path-password and happy-path-cancel.
//     The full GET /me E2E is covered by e2e/profile/me.json.
//
// - T-36 (login blocked after 30-day grace period):
//     Requires manipulating deleted_at to a value 31 days in the past.
//     Not possible via API. Covered by store_test.go T-36.
//
// - T-37 to T-42 (background purge worker):
//     Worker tests are not HTTP tests. Covered by worker_test.go.
//
// - Individual validation variants for telegram_auth fields (empty hash, missing auth_date):
//     Representative cases confirmed in telegram-guards folder.
//     Exhaustive variants covered by handler_test.go.
//
// - Audit row event types and metadata (account_deletion_requested etc.):
//     Covered by store_test.go.
